title: Asian stocks down on weak China data, auto shares sell-off
text: Photo: Mark Lennihan, AP FILE - This Jan. 4, 2010 file photo shows an entrance to a Wall Street subway station in New York. Another slide in Volkswagen's share price combined with renewed worries over China's economy to roil global markets Tuesday, Sept. 22, 2015. FILE - This Jan. 4, 2010 file photo shows an entrance to a Wall... SEOUL, South Korea (AP) — Asian stock markets declined Wednesday as a global sell-off given impetus by the Volkswagen emissions scandal was exacerbated by weak Chinese factory data.
